^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Now, let me discuss the concept of the "captain" of the hand. On every auction, one person is the captain and the other is the subordinate. The captain is the one who takes charge of the auction, deciding how high to go and what to play in. The subordinate mostly just answers the captain's questions. On most hands, responder is the captain. That means, responder is ultimately responsible for getting to the correct contract. For example, on this hand, once South opens, North is the captain.
