^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|On most hands, particularly in NT, you tend to signal with low cards rather than high cards because signaling high cards tends to give up tricks. The low card means you don't like the suit. In suit contracts, on the other hand, you often can signal a high card when you like that suit because length does not matter in suits, as declarer will tend to be able to trump our suit after the second or third round typically. |
